    "summary": "As Head of Corporate Governance and PMO at Amarla, I lead the legal department of the company and ensure delivery of projects. A strategic and results-driven lawyer and IT transformation professional, I motivate and lead global teams to successful execution through vision planning, deep understanding of the business and technology expertise. \n\nAs a lawyer, I negotiated and drafted mergers and acquisitions agreements for major global companies in Baker McKenzie and led several due diligence processes. In the technology area, I increased productivity at the firm by making technical decisions and deploying innovative technology software that delivered significant impact to the work of over 13k professionals and facilitated synergies to ensure sustainable growth. \n\nI build trust-based relationships with C-level and diverse stakeholders. I\u2019m a strong negotiator with the ability to influence and see things from a broad perspective. Connecting and engaging with others and building relationships is my passion. This extends to my personal life where involving myself in the community is paramount to me \u2014 acted as co-chair of the Hispanic Network at Baker McKenzie, and as member of the fundraising committee in the Associate Board of Merit School of Music in Chicago. \n\nI'm a multi-lingual Italian/USA/Venezuelan citizen. Also, I complemented my career by completing an MBA at Chicago\u2019s Booth School of Business in 2019. \n\nI enjoy an active lifestyle participating in a variety of sports (marathons, triathlons, ski, yoga), and I love to explore the world and diverse cultures through travel, reading, and attending classical music concerts/operas and museum exhibits.\n\nCore competencies:\n\u2022\tNegotiation and Deal Creation \n\u2022\tMergers and Acquisitions\n\u2022\tStrategic Thinking\n\u2022\tTransformational Change\n\u2022\tInfluential Relationship Building\n\u2022\tInnovative Solution Creation\n\u2022\tPersuasive Communications\n\u2022\tBuilding and Leading Successful Teams",
